  <div class="article-byline__content">
      <div class="article-byline__written-by">
    <strong>Written by</strong> <strong><script>function ga4_link115() { window.dataLayer.push(JSON.parse('{"event":"default_event"}')) }</script><a href="https://reviewed.usatoday.com/authors/matt-smith" onclick="ga4_link115()">Matthew S. Smith</a></strong>, <strong><script>function ga4_link116() { window.dataLayer.push(JSON.parse('{"event":"default_event"}')) }</script><a href="https://reviewed.usatoday.com/authors/mark-knapp" onclick="ga4_link116()">Mark Knapp</a></strong>, and <strong><script>function ga4_link117() { window.dataLayer.push(JSON.parse('{"event":"default_event"}')) }</script><a href="https://reviewed.usatoday.com/authors/jonathan-hilburg" onclick="ga4_link117()">Jonathan Hilburg</a></strong>
  </div>



    <p class="article-byline__pub-dates">
      Updated May  2, 2024
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

              <p></p>
<p>The best gaming monitor looks different depending on what you need. Maybe you’re after a 21:9 aspect ratio. Maybe you’re after a higher resolution, so a 1440p gaming monitor or even 4K, or to upgrade to a higher refresh rate to complement that <script>function ga4_link118() { window.dataLayer.push(JSON.parse('{"event":"click_inarticle"}')) }</script><a href="https://reviewed.usatoday.com/gaming/content/nvidia-geforce-rtx-4090-review" onclick="ga4_link118()">top-tier graphics card</a> you just bought. Or maybe you want to upgrade to one of the best curved gaming monitors, which can make a noticeable difference in the way you work and play. </p>

<p>The best gaming monitors also support adaptive sync, including AMD FreeSync and Nvidia G-Sync, which reduces screen tearing while gaming, 1ms response times or lower, and have good HDR capabilities.</p>

<p>While good gaming monitors can be expensive, they aren't all created equal. If you want the best 24-inch monitor, look no further than the <strong>Acer Predator XB253Q GW</strong>     <span class="inline-affiliate">
      (<script>function ga4_link119() { window.dataLayer.push(JSON.parse('{"event":"click_inarticle"}')) }</script><a rel="sponsored" class="conversion" target="_blank" data-gaaction="Clicks" data-gacategory="Affiliate Link" data-galabel="Amazon - Amazon" data-quote-url-for="amazon" href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B08R6H9SM5?tag=rvwtbrn-20&amp;linkCode=ogi&amp;th=1&amp;psc=1&amp;language=en_US&amp;asc_source=direct&amp;asc_campaign=21331&amp;asc_refurl=https%3A%2F%2Freviewed.usatoday.com%2Fgaming%2Fbest-right-now%2Fthe-best-gaming-monitors" onclick="ga4_link119()">available at Amazon</a>)
    </span>
. It gives you the feel of an extra big, extra fast gaming monitor for hundreds less than the average ultra wide-screen display. However, if you don't mind going a bit bigger, our list has several great choices, some of which are speedier or offer better image quality without breaking the bank.
</p>
<div>
  <figure data-image-attachment>
    <figure class="image-wrapper">
      <img alt="A photo of the Acer Predator XB253Q GW, the best gaming monitor on a desk" class="lazyload blur-up attachment" eager="false" data-portal-copyright="Reviewed / Matthew S. Smith" data-src="https://reviewed-com-res.cloudinary.com/image/fetch/s--YmUFGlOQ--/b_white,c_limit,cs_srgb,f_auto,fl_progressive.strip_profile,g_center,q_auto,w_792/https://reviewed-production.s3.amazonaws.com/attachment/0fff3e113d024bc8/reviewed-best-monitor.jpg" style="aspect-ratio: 1.78;" src="https://reviewed-com-res.cloudinary.com/image/fetch/s--94NFZU2K--/b_white,c_limit,cs_srgb,f_auto,fl_progressive.strip_profile,g_center,q_1,w_792/https://reviewed-production.s3.amazonaws.com/attachment/0fff3e113d024bc8/reviewed-best-monitor.jpg">
