<p>The Samsung Odyssey Neo G9 is a 49-inch super-ultrawide behemoth that will dominate most gaming desks, wrapping around you with an aggressive, immersive curve.</p>

<p>This is a <script>function ga4_link144() { window.dataLayer.push(JSON.parse('{"event":"click_inarticle","link_location":"product_widget"}')) }</script><a href="https://reviewed.usatoday.com/televisions/features/what-mini-led-tv" onclick="ga4_link144()">Mini-LED monitor</a> with 2048 dimming zones that can operate independently, boosting contrast and dark-level performance beyond other gaming monitors. It’s not as good as <script>function ga4_link145() { window.dataLayer.push(JSON.parse('{"event":"click_inarticle","link_location":"product_widget"}')) }</script><a href="https://reviewed.usatoday.com/televisions/features/oled-qled-uled-whats-the-difference" onclick="ga4_link145()">OLED</a> but offers similar advantages such as deep, inky black levels and a lack of unsightly bright spots along the edges of the display. </p>

